title: BULLETBALL Blizzard
body_text:
W v. A TEN:
The Last Encounter of 2008!
TEN. That's a pretty powerful number.
2007's infamous rivalry completes yet another 12 months, and what better way to close out this most-memorable of years than with one last battle. WvA TEN included the best of the best from the enduring feud. The homeland defenders came prepared with legends the likes of "Killer" Kerr, "Punter" Wolf, and future season finale headliner Michelle Mullins. WALL indeed had its shares of superstars, but were unable to capture the victory on this snowy December night.
The massive Team ALL faction was equipped to the max. Tronolone, DiBuccio, Krott, Londono, among others refused to fall for a second consecutive outing.
Flash Results by Game
WALL: 3, 7, 8
ALL: 1, 2, 4, 5, 6,
The YEARBOOK
Team ALL TEN: Krott, Londono, Megill, Yochum
(Manasquan)
; Baggerly, Edwards, Teiltelbaum
(Ocean Township)
; Tronolone, V. Winston
(Monmouth Regional)
; Smalls
(Calvary Academy)
; DiBuccio
(Allentown)
.
Team WALL TEN: Chris Adams, Eamon Fitzpatrick, Justin Wolf, Kevin Fitzpatrick, Melissa Kerr, Michelle Mullins, Ryan Letsche.
The Rules
: Classic two-team match-up.
The Match
: Team ALL defeated Team WALL, 5 - 3, in Round TEN. WALL leads the series however 6 to 4.
Moments & Stars
: Joey Smalls's faceshot on Chris Adams, knocking off his glasses; Justin Wolf unleashing his inner rage during Game 7; Melissa Kerr's backside soaking wet after catching a ball; Michael Edwards showing up to simply throw one ball
Attendance
: 18, comprised of 14 men and 4 women
New Players
: Orion Baggerly
Other Notes
: DODGEBALL 167 was fifth
Snow War
making it the 33rd
